This new evaluation is based on an R-matrix analysis of reactions  825 1451
in the 17O system at neutron energies below 7 MeV.  In addition to 825 1451
the n+16O channel, we included alpha+13C configurations, but no    825 1451
excited-state channels, even though 7 MeV is slightly above the    825 1451
n+16O* threshold. Experimental data were included for the          825 1451
reactions 16O(n,n)16O, 16O(n,alpha)13C, 13C(alpha,n)16O, and       825 1451
13C(alpha,alpha)13C. Most of the new data added to the analysis    825 1451
since the last evaluation were for the alpha+13C reactions.        825 1451
Fitting these data required a somewhat different 17O level         825 1451
structure, especially for the resonances in the 6-7 MeV range. The 825 1451
structure at lower energies remains much the same, but with some   825 1451
minor differences in the positions and widths of the resonances.   825 1451
The results from the analysis were joined smoothly in the 6.5-7.5  825 1451
MeV region to the previous evaluation, which extends to 150 MeV.   825 1451
                                                                   825 1451
Although the previous modification of the evaluation done by P.R.  825 1451
Page (VII.1) lowered the (n,alpha) reaction by 32% up to 8.9 MeV   825 1451
to better agree with the normalization of the new measurement of   825 1451
Harissopulos et al. [Ha05], the new R-matrix analysis found, as    825 1451
before, a scale for this cross section that is about 6% below the  825 1451
original normalization of the Bair and Haas [Ba73] measurement.    825 1451
Thus, the effect of the previous modification of the (n,alpha)     825 1451
reaction is essentially reversed in this new evaluation.           825 1451
                                                                   825 1451
The capture (MT=102) was updated by including at energies up to 2  825 1451
MeV the results of the R-matrix fit to the 17O(g,n) data by R.J.   825 1451
Holt et al. [PRC18, 1962 (1978)], and the 16O(n,g) data of Tokyo   825 1451
Inst. Technology.  Above 2 MeV, the direct/semidirect cross sec-   825 1451
tions calculated with the CoH3 code were used, renormalized to     825 1451
the R-matrix result at 2 MeV.                                      825 1451
                                                                   825 1451
An important addition to this evaluation are the covariance files  825 1451
for the cross sections (file 33) and for the L=1 elastic           825 1451
scattering Legendre coefficient (mu-bar, file 34).  They were      825 1451
obtained for MT=2 and MT=800 at energies up to 7 MeV by propagat-  825 1451
ing the parameter covariances from the R-matrix analysis to the    825 1451
final data using the appropriate derivatives (sensitivities) with  825 1451
respect to those parameters.  Like the other data in the evalua-   825 1451
tion, the covariances exhibit a great deal of structure with ener- 825 1451
gy up to about 7 MeV, but are approximated with smoothly varying   825 1451
functions above that energy, obtained by extrapolating the 33-     825 1451
group-averaged covariances to 20 MeV, and continuing to 150 MeV.   825 1451
Coarse-grid covariances for some of the other reactions came from  825 1451
the low-fi covariances produced by Kawano in 2008.                 825 1451
